How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

The coronavirus pandemic ended the screen time debate: Screens won. We all now find ourselves on our screens for school, for work and for connecting with family and friends during this time of social distancing and increased isolation.

But should we be worried about this excessive screen use right now? Or should we finally get over it and embrace the benefits of our digital devices?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should use the extra time on screens to connect with people, to share information, and to help each other.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should use the extra time on screens to learn, to teach, and to share knowledge.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should use the extra time on screens to create, to make, and to share.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We can share our thoughts, our feelings, and our ideas with the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We can connect with people we've never met, and share our lives with them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We need to embrace technology, and use it to help us.
